[Data by country, area, or territory for 24 Aug 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20AUG24_1629915834.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 20.3% of daily case numbers and 17.5% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 82.06 million cases. The USA reported over 42 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Brazil (14 404); 6 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 6 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 27.8% of daily case numbers and 23.9% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 63.94 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (6 cases), Sweden, Switzerland (9 cases), and Kazakhstan, among others; 17 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 8 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 13.8% of daily case numbers and 13.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 14.17 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (38 657) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, Morocco, Libya, Occupied Palestinian Territory, and UAE. Jordan and Lebanon reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 4.7% of daily case numbers and 6.6% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.51 million cases. South Africa (7632) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours, followed by Botswana and Benin. Ethiopia, Kenya, Zambia, Algeria, Nigeria, and Ghana reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Cameroon, Uganda, Gabon, and Congo, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 16.7% of daily case numbers and 11.7% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.99 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 22 000 cases), followed by Japan, Malaysia, Viet Nam, French Polynesia, South Korea, Mongolia, Australia, and Fiji.

- The South East Asia region reported 16.5% of the daily newly reported cases and 26.3% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 40.66 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 25 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Indonesia (19 106), Thailand (17 165), Bangladesh (5249), Myanmar (2506), and Nepal (2020). Additionally, Sri Lanka and Maldives have not reported any cases for many days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 24 Aug 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

